THIS IS JUST A VERY LONG WINDED COMPLAINT ABOUT THIS PARTICULAR FANFICTION. AND HOW ITS WHUMP IS ACTUALLY VERY SHALLOW. AND IM FEELING DISCONTENT.

im thinking about a certain musical for that last one. that ive seen recently. but anyways...... characters hurting.... i feel like there always should at least be a secondary and/or tertiary purpose for making a character suffer. beyond just wanting to see them suffer

i guess there could be narrative reasons pain happens also..... but i like it when its specifically about the characters...... besides... hurt is a form of conflict i feel... or at least it can be manifested from conflict. not just physical. it can be entirely emotional too

if a character gets hurt trying to protect a friend who had turned their back them for a while but the character saves them anyways wouldnt that make second chara feel something? make them second guess. feel regret. one characters hurt spurs a different kind of pain in another

if a character is being tortured but refuses to betray their friends and withstands that pain to their breaking point, doesnt that show resilience? a test of character? theyre hurting but its for a purpose, its a purpose that holds value to them

if a character is injured and in the vicinty their friend sees this and instantly acts without thinking to help them doesnt that show a extremely close bond? a friendship that displays how much they care and value that person?

its not simple as just..... making a character feel fear and pain...... thats simply reactive. obvious emotional response. but it should be deeper than that shouldnt it? i keep on thinking about examples from fanfiction. my own and others.

or does it enrich the character? does it further their development? does it affect their Character, who they are as a person? or does it in fact serve to reveal or display facets of ANOTHER character whos by their side. does the pain of one emotional affect the other(s)

like.....what is this pain and suffering Doing for the character.... is it exploring them? is it exposing a side we dont really see? is the way they handle the hurt unique to themself? does it tell something about that character in some subtle way?

.... hm............. im continuing to read that mk whump fic from the other day and hm..... i think...... whump has more value...... if it actually means something.... if theres actually a point to it.... An Emotional, Relevant To The Character point.... some sorta meaningfulness
